-- pd.package: FTD lobster package
name: fastn-community.github.io/lobster-font

This FTD font `lobster` package is for your ftd web projects. To Use this
lobster inside `FTD` project follow below instructions.

-- ds.h3: How to use lobster?

-- ds.code: Add this to your FASTN.ftd
lang: ftd

\-- fastn.dependency: fastn-community.github.io/lobster-font

-- ds.markdown: 

After adding lobster dependency inside you `FASTN.ftd` file, You need to add
lobster assets and import it inside you `ftd` file where you are using this
font for your custom font types. To include lobster into your `ftd` file
follow below instructions.

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd

\-- import: fastn-community.github.io/lobster-font/assets as lobster-assets


-- ds.h3: How to create a custom lobster type? 

-- ds.markdown: 

How to use `ftd.type` to create a custom font `types` using lobster? 

We don't recommend creating custom types. We recommend to use 
our [lobster-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/lobster-typography)

If you're using [lobster-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/lobster-typography) 
and still your designer has introduced new font size which is not included or 
part of our [lobster-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/lobster-typography) 
then only define custom types. 

We hope you shouldn't need to define a custom type.

Below is an example of creating a custom `ftd.type` using lobster.

-- ds.rendered:

-- ds.rendered.input:

\-- ftd.type lobster-size-12-desktop:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $lobster-assets.fonts.Lobster


\-- ftd.type lobster-size-12-mobile:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $lobster-assets.fonts.Lobster

\-- ftd.responsive-type lobster-size-12-400:
desktop: $lobster-size-12-desktop
mobile: $lobster-size-12-mobile

-- ds.rendered.output:

-- ftd.text: 
role: $lobster-size-12-400
color: $inherited.colors.text-strong

`font-size: 12px, font-weight: 400` 

üëâ The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog 

